<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="620" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">640.0031 Danube/153</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a Conversation
                            With the Rumanian Minister (<persName>Davila</persName>)</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-19">May 19, 1932</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>During the call of the Rumanian Minister today he asked me about the Danubian
                        matter. I told him I had talked it over with <persName corresp="#p_TAP1">Tardieu</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BE2">Beneš</persName> and
                        several others. The Minister said he thought it was important to get Germany
                        in; that Germany needed the help of the rest and they needed Germany; that
                        originally it had been proposed as a Danubian affair, but he had begun to
                        think that the interest of Germany would be important.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">H[<hi rend="smallcaps">enry</hi>] L. S[<hi rend="smallcaps">timson</hi>]</persName>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>